  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Geometric feature extraction focuses on quantifying the size and position of facial features, including the nose, lips, forehead, chin, and eyes.",
    "These attributes are encapsulated within a facial geometry feature vector.",
    "Geometric feature extraction employs various geometric interactions, such as points, stretches, and angles, between these components to encode the features.",
    "In contrast, appearance-based feature extraction employs either a single image filter or a combination of filters applied to the entire image or specific regions to discern changes in texture and shape [8].",
    "Furthermore, a range of computational models and methods for processing visual data are employed in feature extraction."
  ],
